# Walkthrough - Resilient Chat Sync ("utf8: invalid string" fix)

I have implemented a resilient synchronization strategy to prevent corrupt chat messages from blocking the entire sync process.

## Changes Made

### [Chat Sync Layer](file:///c:/Users/elink/./gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/sync.ts)

#### [MODIFY] [sync.ts](file:///c:/Users/elink/./gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/sync.ts)
- Modified [syncConversation](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/sync.ts#4-113) to handle insertion failures at the individual message level. 
- If a bulk insert fails (often due to encryption issues with corrupt strings), it now falls back to inserting messages one-by-one and skipping any that cause an error.

#### [MODIFY] [db.ts](file:///c:/Users/elink/./gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/db.ts)
- Improved [sanitizeMessage](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/db.ts#18-40) with an [ensureString](file:///c:/Users/elink/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/MomNest/heart-lens-studio-main/src/lib/db.ts#20-25) helper to strictly guarantee that all encrypted fields are valid strings before they reach the database middleware.

## Verification Results

### Manual Verification
- The sync process now completes even if corrupt messages are encountered.
- "Good" messages are successfully displayed while corrupt ones are skipped and logged as warnings in the console.
- Memory safety and data integrity are maintained by strictly sanitizing all incoming message fields.

